horror_movies_ranking <- movie_data %>%
  filter(Genre == "Horror,Thriller") %>%
  arrange(Rank) %>%
  select(Rank,Title, revenue) %>%
  filter(!is.na(revenue))


view(horror_movies_ranking)

ggplot(horror_movies_ranking, aes(x = Rank, y = revenue)) +
  geom_point(color = "blue", size = 1) +
  geom_smooth(method = "lm", se = FALSE, color = "red") +
  labs(title = "Revenue vs Rank for Horror Thriller Movies",
       x = "Rank",
       y = "Revenue (Millions)") +
  theme_minimal()

average_revenue_by_genre <- highest_rev %>%
  filter(!is.na(revenue)) %>%  
  separate_rows(Genre, sep = ",") %>%  
  group_by(Genre) %>%
  summarize(avg_revenue = mean(revenue, na.rm = TRUE)) %>%  
  arrange(desc(avg_revenue))

Is there a signifcant difference in average revenue between the top genres?

top_two_rev <- average_revenue_by_genre %>%
  arrange(-avg_revenue) %>%
  top_n(2) %>%
  left_join(movie_data %>% 
              separate_rows(Genre, sep = ",") %>%
              group_by(Genre) %>%
              summarize(
                sd = sd(revenue, na.rm = TRUE),  
                n = n()  # Sample size
              ), by = "Genre")
## Selecting by avg_revenue
print(top_two_rev)
## # A tibble: 2  4
##   Genre     avg_revenue    sd     n
##   <chr>           <dbl> <dbl> <int>
## 1 Animation        191.  120.    49
## 2 Adventure        154.  138.   259
xbar1 <- top_two_rev$avg_revenue[1]
xbar2 <- top_two_rev$avg_revenue[2]
s1 <- top_two_rev$sd[1]
s2 <- top_two_rev$sd[2]
n1 <- top_two_rev$n[1]
n2 <- top_two_rev$n[2]


w_numer <- (s1^2/n1 + s2^2/n2)^2
w_denom <- (s1^4/(n1^2*(n1-1)) + s2^4/(n2^2*(n2-1)))
w <- w_numer / w_denom

pt_est <- xbar1 - xbar2
se <- sqrt(s1^2/n1 + s2^2/n2)

cv <- qt(0.95, df = w)
c(pt_est - cv*se, pt_est + cv*se)
## [1]  5.190749 68.902011

The confidence interval is 5.190749 68.902011. The interval suggests that the difference in average revenue between the two genres lies between 5.19 and 68.90 million dollars. Because the interval is positive, it indicates the the Genre: Animation is likely to have a signficant higher revenue comapred to the Genre: Avdventure. The Interval also does not include zero, which indicates that it is statistically significant at the confeince level 95%.However, dthe sample size for animation is signifcantlly smaller than the adventure sample size. This can indicate the the estimated average revenue for this genre may not fully represent its average revenue in the population.

How have ratings changed over the years?
